data.title: Visits by Foreign Leaders
data.text: President Vaclav Havel Attended dedication of the Holocaust Memorial Museum and met with President Clinton on April 21. April 20–22, 1993 Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus Working visit. May 3–5, 1995 President Vaclav Havel Attended dedication of the Czech and Slovak Museum and Library in Cedar Rapids, Iowa. October 21, 1995 Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus Met with President Clinton during a private visit. September 30–October 1, 1996 President Vaclav Havel State Visit. September 15–18, 1998 President Vaclav Havel Attended NATO’s 50th Anniversary Summit. April 23–25, 1999 Prime Minister Milos Zeman Working visit. November 7–9, 1999 Prime Minister Milos Zeman Met with President Bush November 9 during a private visit. November 7–10, 2001 President Vaclav Havel Working visit. Also dedicated a monument to President Thomas Masaryk. September 17–19, 2002 Prime Minister Vladimir Spidla Working visit. July 14–17, 2003 President Vaclav Klaus Attended the funeral of Former President Reagan. June 11, 2004 President Vaclav Klaus Working visit March 8, 2005 Prime Minister Mirek Topolanek Working visit. February 25–28, 2008 Prime Minister Jan Fischer Attended the Nuclear Security Summit. April 12–13, 2010 Prime Minister Petr Necas Working visit. October 27, 2011 President Vaclav Klaus Attended the NATO Summit Meeting in Chicago, IL. May 20–21, 2012 Prime Minister Bohuslav Sobotka Working visit. November 17, 2014 Prime Minister Bohuslav Sobotka Attended the Nuclear Security Summit. March 31–April 1, 2016
